# External API Integration Guidelines

## External Traffic Management
- Use [app/Http/Controllers/ExternalTrafficController.php](mdc:app/Http/Controllers/ExternalTrafficController.php) for external traffic
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Use [app/Services/External/ExternalTrafficService.php](mdc:app/Services/External/ExternalTrafficService.php) for business logic

## Message Handling
- Use [app/Services/External/ExternalMessageService.php](mdc:app/Services/External/ExternalMessageService.php) for message processing
- Use [app/Services/External/ExternalEditedMessageService.php](mdc:app/Services/External/ExternalEditedMessageService.php) for message editing
- Implement proper message validation and sanitization

## DTOs and Data Structures
- Use [app/DTOs/External/ExternalMessageDto.php](mdc:app/DTOs/External/ExternalMessageDto.php) for message data
- Use [app/DTOs/External/ExternalUpdateDto.php](mdc:app/DTOs/External/ExternalUpdateDto.php) for updates
- Use [app/DTOs/ExternalSourceDto.php](mdc:app/DTOs/ExternalSourceDto.php) for source information

## Source Management
- Use [app/Services/External/Source/ExternalSourceService.php](mdc:app/Services/External/Source/ExternalSourceService.php) for source management
- Use [app/Services/External/Source/ExternalSourceTokensService.php](mdc:app/Services/External/Source/ExternalSourceTokensService.php) for token management
- Implement proper token rotation and security

## API Security
- Validate all incoming requests
- Implement rate limiting for external APIs
- Use secure token storage and transmission
- Log all external API interactions for monitoring
